programme.title: Decisión extrema

programme.title: En el ojo del huracán

programme.title: 100 Women
programme.desc: From building herself a reputation as a rebellious star in the 1990s to being made a dame by King Charles in 2024, Tracey Emin is an icon in the contemporary art world. With a career spanning over three decades, her pieces tackle issues of sex, pain and the female experience in a deliberately confessional way. But Emin's life hasn't always been filled with awards and royal recognition. Over the past few years, she has survived an aggressive cancer, opened an art school and produced paintings and sculptures with renewed intensity. Twenty-five years after her famous installation My Bed was nominated for a Turner Prize and first exhibited in London, the artist sat down with BBC 100 Women to talk about the person behind the artwork and the legacy she hopes to leave behind.

programme.title: The Naked Gun: From the Files of Police Squad!
programme.desc: While investigating the shooting of a colleague, disaster-prone police lieutenant Frank Drebin uncovers a plot to assassinate the Queen during her visit to Los Angeles. However, after he is sacked from the force by the mayor, the cop has to operate beneath the radar to get to the bottom of the conspiracy. Comedy, with Leslie Nielsen, Priscilla Presley and Ricardo Montalban

programme.title: Straightheads
programme.desc: A woman and her lover are attacked by a gang while driving down a remote country road, an experience that leaves them traumatised. Later returning to the area in the wake of her father's death, she encounters one of her attackers by chance and sees the opportunity to take revenge. Thriller, starring Gillian Anderson and Danny Dyer

programme.title: It Came from Beneath the Sea
programme.desc: The captain of a nuclear submarine battles a gigantic octopus threatening to destroy San Francisco. Monster adventure, starring Kenneth Tobey, Faith Domergue and Donald Curtis, with special effects by Ray Harryhausen

programme.title: Enemy Mine
programme.desc: In the midst of a war between humans and aliens, two space pilots from opposite sides are marooned together on an inhospitable planet and are forced to set aside their mutual animosity to survive. Sci-fi adventure, starring Dennis Quaid, Louis Gossett Jr and Brion James

programme.title: Napoleon Dynamite
programme.desc: A socially inept high-school student and his lonely unemployed brother find their eccentric home life thrown into upheaval when their meddling uncle comes to stay. The teenage oddball tries to make the best of his changing circumstances, while putting all his skills to the task of helping his new best friend win the class presidency. Comedy, starring Jon Heder, Efren Ramirez and Haylie Duff

programme.title: My Best Friend's Wedding
programme.desc: A food critic realises she is in love with her best friend just as he announces he is going to marry another woman. Determined to have him to herself, she heads for the wedding with the intention of sabotaging the ceremony - but persuading the groom to give up on his bride-to-be proves harder than expected. Romantic comedy, starring Julia Roberts, Dermot Mulroney, Cameron Diaz and Rupert Everett

programme.title: Flight of the Phoenix
programme.desc: The crew and passengers of a cargo plane are left stranded in the Gobi desert after a crash. They embark on a desperate plan to return to civilisation - by building a new plane out of the wreckage of the old one. Action adventure remake, starring Dennis Quaid, Tyrese Gibson, Giovanni Ribisi, Miranda Otto and Hugh Laurie

programme.title: Oblivion
programme.desc: A repairman is assigned to salvage the remaining resources from Earth, which has been left a devastated wasteland after a war with an alien race. He discovers a human survivor on the surface of the planet, an encounter that exposes secrets from the past that threaten the future of the human race. Sci-fi adventure, starring Tom Cruise and Morgan Freeman

programme.title: Underwater
programme.desc: Nora Price is a mechanical engineer at the Kepler drilling station, seven miles beneath the surface of the Pacific Ocean. She and a small crew fight for survival after a tremor causes catastrophic failures to the base's integrity. Meanwhile, in the inky void, something unspeakable lurks, waiting to attack. Sci-fi thriller, starring Kristen Stewart, Mamoudou Athie and Vincent Cassell

programme.title: Slumdog Millionaire
programme.desc: An uneducated teenager from the Mumbai slums is only one question away from winning a quiz show, but the authorities are reluctant to believe a youngster from such a humble background could succeed without cheating. Under questioning, he tells a police inspector the eventful story of his life - and how he came to know so much. Danny Boyle's Oscar-winning drama, starring Dev Patel and Freida Pinto

programme.title: Turner & Hooch
programme.desc: A Californian detective investigating the murder of a local man by drug smugglers has only one witness to help him solve the case - the large, smelly dog that belonged to the victim, which is about to turn the detective's well-ordered existence into chaos. Family comedy, starring Tom Hanks, Mare Winningham and Craig T Nelson

programme.title: Close Encounters of the Third Kind
programme.desc: An electrical repairman sees a fleet of UFOs and develops an increasing fascination with mountain-shaped forms, driving his wife to despair. Meanwhile, a single mother has a similar fixation after her son mysteriously vanishes, and a team of scientists investigates a series of strange events around the world. Eventually, they are all drawn to a mountain where aliens are about to make contact. Steven Spielberg's sci-fi drama, starring Richard Dreyfuss, Francois Truffaut and the late Teri Garr

programme.title: Clear and Present Danger
programme.desc: A CIA analyst gets caught up in the Colombian drug trade while trying to track down terrorists responsible for the murder of a close friend of the US president - but his investigations point to illegal activity and corruption at the very top of government. Action thriller, based on Tom Clancy's novel, with Harrison Ford reprising his role from Patriot Games alongside Willem Dafoe, Anne Archer and James Earl Jones

programme.title: Deep Impact
programme.desc: A TV reporter investigating a presidential misdemeanour stumbles on evidence that a comet is on a collision course with Earth, threatening the future of the human race. Meanwhile, an astronaut prepares to lead his crew on a do-or-die mission to intercept the danger. Sci-fi drama, starring Robert Duvall, Tea Leoni, Morgan Freeman and Elijah Wood

programme.title: The Electrical Life of Louis Wain: Interview Special
programme.desc: Stars Benedict Cumberbatch and Claire Foy talk about making director Will Sharpe's eccentric biopic of artist and inventor Louis Wain

programme.title: London Has Fallen
programme.desc: World leaders gather in London for the funeral of the British Prime Minister, unaware they have been led into a trap. A terrorist plans to kill them all, and devastate the city, and the only people in a position to stop him are the President of the United States and the indomitable head of his secret service. Action thriller sequel to Olympus Has Fallen, starring Gerard Butler, Aaron Eckhart and Morgan Freeman

programme.title: Arkansas
programme.desc: Kyle and Swin live by the orders of a drug kingpin called Frog, who they have never met. When a deal goes horribly wrong, the consequences are deadly. Thriller, starring Liam Hemsworth, John Malkovich and Clark Duke, who also co-wrote and directed

programme.title: Sweet Country
programme.desc: An aged Aboriginal farmhand shoots a white man in self defence and goes on the run as a posse gathers to hunt him down. Australian period drama, starring Hamilton Morris, Bryan Brown and Sam Neill

programme.title: BSL Zone: Sign2Win
programme.desc: BSL Zone's first deaf gameshow. Three teams have their BSL language and deaf cultural knowledge tested with a prize of £1000 going to the winner

programme.title: Journey to the Center of the Earth
programme.desc: An explorer discovers a prehistoric monster-infested world deep beneath Earth's crust and faces a tough ordeal escaping the predatory attacks of the creatures as he tries to guide his team back to safety. Sci-fi adventure based on Jules Verne's novel, starring Pat Boone, James Mason, Arlene Dahl and Diane Baker

programme.title: The 300 Spartans
programme.desc: The ruler of the Persian empire vows to expand his realm by conquering Greece. The king of Sparta steps forward to defend his homeland and the other kingdoms of Greece, but when he is betrayed by a political council, he finds himself without an army and must fend off the vast invading army with a mere 300 warriors. Historical drama, starring Richard Egan, Ralph Richardson and Diane Baker

programme.title: Tora! Tora! Tora!
programme.desc: Fact-based Second World War drama recounting the bombing of Pearl Harbour from both the Japanese and American perspectives, reconstructing the events leading up to the devastating attack on the US naval base in 1941. Starring Martin Balsam, So Yamamura, Joseph Cotten, James Whitmore and Jason Robards

programme.title: The Eagle
programme.desc: A Roman centurion seeks to restore his father's honour by recovering the standard of a legion that disappeared. Accompanied by his British slave, he makes a dangerous journey north of Hadrian's Wall into the Scottish Highlands, territory occupied by hostile tribes. Action adventure, starring Channing Tatum, Jamie Bell, Mark Strong and Donald Sutherland

programme.title: Fisherman's Friends: One and All
programme.desc: Following the success of their first album, the Fisherman's Friends struggle to adjust to their new-found fame and work towards a second album. Comedy sequel, starring James Purefoy, Sam Swainsbury and Dave Johns

programme.title: Antwone Fisher
programme.desc: A troubled Navy recruit is prone to violent outbursts and is ordered to see a psychiatrist, who gradually helps the mentally scarred sailor to come to terms with his past and abusive childhood. Fact-based drama, directed by and starring Denzel Washington. With Derek Luke, Joy Bryant and Salli Richardson

programme.title: El hombre del norte

programme.title: Jarhead - El infierno espera
programme.desc: Sam Mendes dirige, a través de la perspectiva de un joven interpretado por Jake Gyllenhaal, una impactante película sobre la guerra del Golfo.

programme.title: Jarhead 2: Tormenta de fuego
programme.desc: El cabo Merrimette y su equipo tienen la misión de reabastecer un remoto puesto cercano a un territorio controlado por los talibanes. El encuentro fortuito con un Navy Seal modificará sus planes.

programme.title: El destino de Júpiter
programme.desc: De las calles de Chicago a galaxias remotas, Jupiter Jones se embarca en una aventura como la heredera de un extraordinario legado de que pudiera alterar el equilibrio del cosmos.

programme.title: Friends - T9, E10: El de la Navidad en Tulsa
programme.desc: Chandler tiene que quedarse en Tulsa durante las Navidades por una fecha de entrega del trabajo. Mónica sospecha lo peor cuando descubre que lo acompaña una compañera de trabajo guapa, Wendy.

programme.title: Friends - T9, E11: En el que Rachel vuelve al trabajo
programme.desc: Cuando Rachel visita su trabajo para presentar a Emma le sorprende descubrir a un trabajador temporal, Gavin, muy guapo, que ha estado haciendo su trabajo mientras ella estaba de baja por maternidad.

programme.title: Friends - T9, E12: El de las ratas de Phoebe
programme.desc: A Rachel le molesta que hayan invitado a su nuevo rival del trabajo, Gavin, a su fiesta de cumpleaños. Mientras, Ross trata de evitar que Joey se acerque con intenciones lascivas a la nueva niñera de Emma, Molly.

programme.title: Friends - T9, E13: El de cuando Mónica canta
programme.desc: Mientras Rachel aclara lo que siente por su compañero de trabajo, Gavin, Ross convence a Chandler para que lo ayude a conocer a mujeres atractivas para poner celosa a Rachel.

programme.title: Friends - T9, E14: El de las citas a ciegas
programme.desc: Joey y Phoebe conspiran para conseguirles citas horribles a Rachel y Ross esperando que apreciar su antigua relación provoque que vuelvan juntos. La cita de Rachel es un triste exdueño de un restaurante, Steve.

programme.title: Friends - T9, E15: El del atraco
programme.desc: Joey desarrolla un método de actuación poco habitual para impresionar a un actor famoso y pomposo, Leonard, durante la audición para su próximo papel de teatro. Mientras, Ross descubre horrorizado quién le robó siendo niño.

programme.title: Friends - T9, E16: El de la operación de senos
programme.desc: Phoebe le pide a su novio, Mike, que se mude con ella pero estar tan cerca del matrimonio causa problemas en la relación. Mientras, como Mónica y Chandler son económicamente inestables, ella le pide un préstamo a Joey en secreto.

programme.title: Friends - T9, E17: El del funeral
programme.desc: Cuando Chandler publica de broma una biografía escandalosa en la página de antiguos alumnos de Ross, este se venga buscando la página de Chandler y haciéndole lo mismo. Ahí comienza una guerra de internet entre los dos amigos.

programme.title: The Big Bang Theory - T9, E09: La permutación platónica
programme.desc: En Acción de Gracias Sheldon y Amy intentan pasar tiempo como amigos y deciden ir al acuario. Penny se percata de cuánto la conoce Leonard.

programme.title: The Big Bang Theory - T9, E10: La reverberación de la melodía
programme.desc: Sheldon no es capaz de quitarse de la cabeza una melodía. Howard y Raj conocen a un fan de su banda. Sheldon le da un ultimatum a Amy.

programme.title: The Big Bang Theory - T9, E11: La excitación del estreno
programme.desc: Sheldon prepara una gran sorpresa para Amy con motivo de su cumpleaños. Leonard, Howard y Raj asisten al estreno de la nueva película de Star Wars.

programme.title: The Big Bang Theory - T9, E12: La sublimación de la venta
programme.desc: Leonard ayuda a Penny a realizar una venta. Stuart se muda de casa de Howard, lo cual hace que él y Bernadette puedan ser felices momentáneamente.

programme.title: The Big Bang Theory - T9, E13: La optimización de la empatía
programme.desc: Después de tener que tratar con un Sheldon enfermo, Leonard, Penny y el grupo intentan darse un gusto pasando un fin de semana sin Sheldon.

programme.title: The Big Bang Theory - T9, E14: La materialización de la abuelita
programme.desc: Sheldon se pone muy contento cuando su Mimau le hace una visita, pero su entusiasmo se disipa rápidamente al ver que no aprueba a Amy. Además, Raj conoce a una chica en la tienda de cómics que hace que se replantee su relación con Emily.

programme.title: The Big Bang Theory - T9, E15: La inmersión de Valentino
programme.desc: Sheldon y Amy presentan una edición especial de "Diversión con banderas" en el día de San Valentín. Mientras tanto, Leonard y Penny lidian con la idea de hacerse mayores, Howard y Bernadette se encuentran una sorpresa en su bañera de hidromasaje.

programme.title: The Big Bang Theory - T9, E16: La reacción positivo-negativa
programme.desc: Cuando el grupo descubre que Bernadette está embarazada, lo celebran cantando en un karaoke.

programme.title: The Big Bang Theory - T9, E17: La experimentación de la celebración
programme.desc: Después de nueve años juntos, el grupo por fin celebra el cumpleaños de Sheldon con algunos invitados especiales, incluyendo a uno de los actores que encarnó a Batman, Adam West.

programme.title: The Big Bang Theory - T9, E18: El deterioro de la soledad
programme.desc: Los chicos intentan patentar una de sus ideas, lo que lleva a Sheldon a redactar un contrato. Las chicas hablan sobre las náuseas de Bernadette.

programme.title: Kung Fu Panda 2
programme.desc: Po y sus amigos luchan para impedir que un villano pavo real conquiste China con una nueva arma mortal, pero el Guerrero Dragón debe aceptar su pasado.

programme.title: Robin Hood: Forajido, héroe, leyenda

programme.title: Pequeños detalles
